                                                                  5229 1451
 Nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-3.2.3 Malta                   5229 1451
 (SVN rev.  4976; source rev.  4972)                              5229 1451
 by M.W.Herman et al [EMP,EMP-man].                               5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 EMPIRE dimensions (dimension.h):                                 5229 1451
  NDNUC= 160  NDEXCLUS= 50  NDEX= 241  NDLW= 100                  5229 1451
  LEVCC= 40  NDLV= 40  NDBR= 40  NDMSCS= 4                        5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                5229 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               5229 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               5229 1451
 of important modules and features:                               5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 5229 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      5229 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  5229 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                5229 1451
   and coworkers                                                  5229 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    5229 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          5229 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 5229 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                5229 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       5229 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      5229 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 5229 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                5229 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               5229 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                5229 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   5229 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                5229 1451
   discrete transitions                                           5229 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                5229 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                5229 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               5229 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 5229 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 5229 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              5229 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  5229 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     5229 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 5229 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                5229 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      5229 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   5229 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      5229 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   5229 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  5229 1451
 - generating covariances                                         5229 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 PARAMETERIZATIONS                                                5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 Following models and parameters were used in the                 5229 1451
 current evaluation:                                              5229 1451
                                                                  5229 1451
 Discrete levels were taken from the RIPL-3+                      5229 1451
 library based on the 2015 version of ENSDF.                      5229 1451
 ENDF formatting enabled                                          5229 1451
 Exclusive emission from CN and target enabled                    5229 1451
 Exclusive spectra available for residues distant                 5229 1451
   from CN up to 2 neut. or 2 prot.                               5229 1451
 Target excited to the level # 3                                  5229 1451
 EMPIRE-specific level densities (J>>K aprox.)                    5229 1451
 HRTW width fluctuation correction calculated  up to  3.00 MeV    5229 1451
 Exciton model calculations with code PCROSS                      5229 1451
 Cluster emission in terms of the Iwamoto-Harada model            5229 1451
 Kalbach systematics angular distributions (see RIPL-1)           5229 1451
 Mean free path parameter in PCROSS set to  1.5 (Recomm:~1.5)     5229 1451
 CN anisotropy calculated using Blatt-Biedenharn coefficients     5229 1451
 CN decay and Direct cross sections added incoherently            5229 1451
 Traditional Hauser-Feschbach Tlj_{CC}(E)=Tlj_{GS}(E-Egs)         5229 1451
 E1 strength function set to RIPL MLO1                            5229 1451
 GDR parameters from RIPL/Exp.data+Plujko systematics             5229 1451
 Gamma-transition multipolarity set to    2                       5229 1451
